{
  "texts": [
    "However, GC often suffers from sophisticated optimization processes and slow convergence, resulting in a time-consuming procedure.",
    "This particularly deteriorates in life-long learning contexts, where regular updates to the condensed graph dataset are a common requirement, as depicted in Figure 7.",
    "To address these challenges, efficient GC methods have been developed to accelerate the condensation process across all components within GC.",
    "To thoroughly explore the mechanisms underlying efficient GC, we break down the conventional GC procedure into three stages: graph encoding, optimization, and graph generation.",
    "These components align with the input, processing, and output stages of GC, respectively."
  ]
}